Police Minister Bheki Cele said authorities are probing how self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife skipped the country. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele said authorities are probing how self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife skipped the country. Cele said he believes the couple should not have been granted bail. READ: SA breaks silence on fugitive Bushiri The Bushiris contravened their bail conditions as they are not allowed to travel outside South Africa. Last week, the couple was granted bail of R200,000 each. READ: Bushiri: I'm not running away from my trial In a statement, the government said they have started a process to extradite Bushiri using the SADC extradition laws. They're facing charges of theft, money laundering and fraud in connection with an alleged R100-million investment scheme. South Africa's government has finally responded to self-proclaimed prophet Shepherd Bushiri and his wife, absconding the country. #DStv403